- xG (expected goals) is a metric measuring the quality of scoring chances; 
- Non-penalty goals are goals scored during open play, excluding penalty shootouts; 
- Assists are passes that lead directly to a goal; 
- Shots are the number of times a player attempts to score; 
- Performance metrics (expected goals, assists, etc.) provide insight into a player's contribution to the match outcome.

